JuniNextServerListIndex.name: JuniNextServerListIndex
JuniNextServerListIndex.description: Coordinate index value allocation for entries in an associated table, by first reading an index value from this object, then creating an entry, having that index value, in the associated table. The DESCRIPTION clause for an object of this type must identify the associated table. A GET of this object returns the next available index value to be used to create an entry in the associated table; or zero, if no valid index value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that index allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously. Unless specified otherwise by its MAX-ACCESS and DESCRIPTION clauses, an object of this type is read-only, and a SET of such an object returns a notWritable error.

ServerListIndex.name: ServerListIndex
ServerListIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each DNS server in the managed system.

juniDnsServerListTable.name: juniDnsServerListTable
juniDnsServerListTable.description: This table contains an entry for each DNS server.

juniDnsServerListEntry.name: juniDnsServerListEntry
juniDnsServerListEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to an associated DNS server.

juniDnsServerListIndex.name: juniDnsServerListIndex
juniDnsServerListIndex.description: The index of the DNS server. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading juniDnsServerListNextIndex.

juniDnsServerListAddress.name: juniDnsServerListAddress
juniDnsServerListAddress.description: The IP address of the DNS server. This object has been replaced by juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddressType and juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddress.

juniDnsServerListRowStatus.name: juniDnsServerListRowStatus
juniDnsServerListRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy

juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddressType.name: juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddressType
juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddressType.description: The type of IP address (IPv4 or IPv6) of the DNS server.

juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddress.name: juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddress
juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddress.description: The IP address of the DNS server. Note: Since this object is used to configure the IPv4 or IPv6 address depending on juniDnsV4V6ServerListAddressType value, it is mandatory to provide the IPv4 or IPv6 address by specifying each octet's positional values explicitly. Example: 1. IPv4 -- 4 octets -- 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 2. IPv6 -- 16 octets -- 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF 0xFF
